data.title: Football Cartophilic Info Exchange
data.text:
Sweetule Products - (SWE-180) Junior Service Quiz

1959

(SWE-180) Junior Service Quiz

Sweetule Products

25 cards (4 football)

Sweetule were a Manchester company but this set seems a little top heavy with Scottish content. I suppose one-club collectors should be looking to get both cards as the answer to each question appears on the following card, except for the question on card no. 25 can be found on card no. 1.

Panini America

Every 10-card pack of 2016 Spectra Soccer will include five autograph or memorabilia cards, three base cards, one die-cut parallel numbered to 65 or less and one base parallel numbered to 75 or less and is expected to cost approximately $350. A combination of soccer stars from the past, present and future.

Six autograph inserts showcase the best and brightest in the world. Panini America continues to bring the biggest names in soccer to trading cards.

10 cards per pack, 1 pack per box, 5 boxes per case.

Due for release on 29 September, 2016.
